.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdiddy-dangled-me-off-17th-floor-balcony-slammed-into-furniture-designers-explosive-claim%2Famp_articleshow%2F115843953.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20gives%20more%20details%20on%20Russia's%20'Oreshnik'%20hypersonic%20missile%2C%20saying%20its%20destructive%20elements%20reach%20over%207%2C000%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vladimir%20Putin%20told%20reporters%20in%20Kazakhstan%20about%20Russia's%20use%20of%20the%20Oreshnik%20missile%20in%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6749cc4bede4eeae392a5d45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EContributor%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20provided%20more%20details%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BOreshnik%26quot%3B%20missile.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20hypersonic%20ballistic%20missile%20was%20first%20used%20by%20Russia%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20November.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPutin%20said%20the%20missile's%20destructive%20elements%20hit%20temperatures%20of%20more%20than%207%2C000%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fen.kremlin.ru%2Fevents%2Fpresident%2Ftranscripts%2F75689%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%20more%20details%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Russia's%20%26quot%3BOreshnik%26quot%3B%20missile%20during%20a%20state%20visit%20to%20Kazakhstan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20first%20used%20the%20Oreshnik%20missile%20in%20Ukraine%20last%20week%2C%20striking%20a%20munitions%20factory%20in%20Dnipro.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutin%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20his%20forces%20had%20tested%20%26quot%3Ba%20non-nuclear%20hypersonic%20ballistic%20missile%2C%26quot%3B%20named%20the%20Oreshnik%2C%20in%20response%20to%20Ukraine's%20use%20of%20US%20and%20UK-supplied%20long-range%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20the%20media%20in%20Kazakhstan%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Putin%20detailed%20some%20more%20of%20the%20Oreshnik's%20characteristics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutin%20called%20the%20missile%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh-precision%20and%20high-power%20weapon%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20equipped%20with%20a%20nuclear%20explosive%20device%2C%20thus%20they%20do%20not%20cause%20environmental%20contamination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20destructive%20elements%20inside%20the%20missile's%20warheads%20hit%20temperatures%20of%20over%204%2C000%20degrees%20Celsius%20(more%20than%207%2C000%20degrees%20Fahrenheit).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20damage%20is%20substantial%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20at%20the%20centre%20is%20reduced%20to%20ash%2C%20breaking%20down%20into%20its%20elemental%20components%2C%20and%20objects%20located%20at%20a%20depth%20of%20three%20or%20four%2C%20possibly%20even%20more%2C%20floors%20below%20are%20affected.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutin%20also%20reiterated%20that%20the%20Oreshnik%20could%20be%20as%20powerful%20as%20a%20nuclear%20strike%20if%20multiple%20were%20fired%20at%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MOD)%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20the%20Oreshnik%20was%20likely%20a%20variant%20of%20the%20Rubezh%20RS-26%20ballistic%20missile%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissilethreat.csis.org%2Fmissile%2Fss-x-31-rs-26-rubezh%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolid-fueled%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20road-mobile%20ballistic%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20said%20that%20the%20missile's%20payload%20observed%20in%20the%20strike%20on%20Dnipro%20was%20%26quot%3Bsix%20groups%20of%20six%20warheads%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20it%20said%20travel%20at%20hypersonic%20speeds%20before%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20missile's%20potential%20range%20is%20particularly%20important%20and%20has%20already%20attracted%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20expert%20commentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20(CSIS)%20Missile%20Defense%20Project%20lists%20the%20Rubezh%20RS-26%20as%20having%20a%20range%20of%20up%20to%205%2C800%20km%20(around%203%2C600%20miles)%2C%20meaning%20it%20could%20strike%20targets%20across%20Europe%20and%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20Australian%20Army%20Maj.%20Gen.%20Mick%20Ryan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FWarintheFuture%2Fstatus%2F1859750111187960181%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20Russia's%20use%20of%20a%20missile%20with%20such%20a%20potential%20range%20was%20a%20clear%20message%20to%20the%20West%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20writing%20on%20X%3A%20%26quot%3BPutin%20isn't%20only%20messaging%20Washington%20D.C.%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20message%20to%20Europe%2C%20not%20only%20about%20their%20support%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20also%20about%20Russia's%20capacity%20and%20willingness%20to%20influence%20policy%20related%20to%20defence%20and%20security%20well%20beyond%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foreshnik-missile-new-details-putin-russia-ukraine-hypersonic-2024%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732971817000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6749ccd2fa0140cdd56639d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foreshnik-missile-new-details-putin-russia-ukraine-hypersonic-2024%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20hypersonic%20ballistic%20missile%20was%20first%20used%20by%20Russia%20in%20an%20attack%20on%20Dnipro%2C%20eastern%20Ukraine%2C%20in%20November.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rrommen%40insider.com%20(Rebecca%20Rommen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foreshnik-missile-new-details-putin-russia-ukraine-hypersonic-2024%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampU