20country%2C%20with%20protestors%20arming%20themselves%20to%20defend%20their%20towns%20and%20launch%20attacks%20on%20the%20Syrian%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20following%20months%2C%20the%20rebels%20fractured%20into%20hundreds%20of%20armed%20groups.%20The%20conflict%20also%20attracted%20jihadist%20extremist%20groups%20like%20HTS--a%20faction%20formerly%20linked%20to%20the%20terrorist%20group%20Al%20Qaeda--%20who%20soon%20became%20one%20of%20the%20dominant%20anti-government%20factions.%20United%20States%20has%20proscribed%20HTS%20as%20a%20terrorist%20group.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20rebel%20groups%20making%20gains%20during%20the%20early%20years%20of%20the%20civil%20war%2C%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20sought%20help%20from%20his%20allies%20for%20his%20regime%20to%20survive.%20Iran%2C%20Syria's%20closest%20ally%2C%20backed%20his%20regime%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%20by%20providing%20advisers%2C%20weapons%2C%20billions%20of%20dollars%20and%20troops%20to%20help%20Mr%20Assad%20maintain%20his%20grip%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20The%20Telegraph.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIranian-backed%20groups%20like%20Hezbollah%20have%20also%20been%20reportedly%20supporting%20Mr%20Assad's%20army%20since%20at%20least%202012.%20Russia%20also%20decided%20to%20back%20the%20government%20forces%20in%202015%2C%20with%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20committing%20Moscow's%20air%20force%20as%20well%20as%20ground%20troops%20to%20ensure%20the%20Syrian%20regime%20did%20not%20fall.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20neighbouring%20Turkey%2C%20another%20major%20player%20in%20the%20war%2C%20threw%20its%20weight%20behind%20the%20opposition%20to%20Mr%20Assad's%20regime.%20Ankara%20used%20rebel%20factions%20in%20Syria%20to%20contain%20the%20Kurdish%20YPG%2C%20that%20dominates%20the%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces%20(SDF).%20According%20to%20Ankara%2C%20the%20group%20is%20an%20extension%20of%20a%20banned%20Kurdish%20rebel%20group%20in%20Turkey%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%